The biggest ice cover on North America 's Great Lakes in decades is backing up important shipping deliveries with 18 freighters , unable to move .
Extraordinary aerial photographs taken above Whitefish Bay on eastern Lake Superior , Ontario , show some of the freighters lined up across a frozen expanse .
They are carrying a variety of goods from Canadian grain to US iron and steel .
The ships desperately need a path cut through the lake by Canadian and US ice breakers .